  "prompt": "What are some good colleges in India that I can still apply to their MBA program for this year\u2019s session?",
  "response": "As of October 2023, many colleges in India still have MBA programs with application deadlines that may extend into the later months of the year. However, the specific application timelines can vary each year, and it's essential to check the official websites of the colleges for the most accurate and updated information. Here are some well-regarded colleges in India where you might find opportunities to apply for their MBA programs:\n\n1. **Indian Institute of Management (IIMs)** - Some of the newer IIMs may have later deadlines for their MBA programs. Check IIMs like IIM Nagpur, IIM Sambalpur, etc.\n\n2. **XLRI Jamshedpur** - Known for its Human Resource Management program, XLRI might have additional admissions rounds.\n\n3. **SP Jain Institute of Management and Research (SPJIMR)** - Check for their admission process, which sometimes has multiple rounds.\n\n4. **Indian School of Business (ISB)** - ISB has multiple admission cycles for its Post Graduate Program in Management (PGP).\n\n5. **Great Lakes Institute of Management** - They offer both 1-year and 2-year MBA programs, with various admission rounds.\n\n6. **T. A. Pai Management Institute (TAPMI)** - This institute may still be accepting applications.\n\n7. **Loyola Institute of Business Administration (LIBA), Chennai** - They might have ongoing admissions for MBA programs.\n\n8. **Narsee Monjee Institute of Management Studies (NMIMS)** - Their MBA programs often have rolling admissions.\n\n9. **Institute of Management Technology (IMT), Ghaziabad** - IMT has a few rounds of admissions, so check for their latest updates.\n\n10. **Jindal Global Business School** - Located in Sonipat, Haryana, they may still be accepting applications.\n\nBe sure to verify the specific program details, prerequisites, and deadlines on the respective college websites. Good luck with your applications!",
